HEADWORD: Juncaceous
<hw>Jun*ca"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Juncate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Of. pertaining to, or
resembling, a natural family of plants (<fam>Juncace⟦ae⟧</fam>), of
which the common rush (<gen>Juncus</gen>) is the type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

